[normal]It would appear that the debate about creating 
[normal]a separate UK Bill of Rights
[normal] has run its course. That being the case
[normal], the British parliaments and courts must learn to take full cognisance of the EU Charter as the main source of rights law 
[normal]throughout the Union and at all levels
[normal]. The Charter is 
[normal]the essential prism through which the ECHR must henceforth be interpreted
[normal] in so far and as long as 
[normal]the UK remains a full member state of the EU. An essential condition of full membership is allegiance to the ECHR and the Charter. 
[normal]Any attempt to reduce the UK’s legal and political adherence to the ECHR and the Charter will jeopardise Britain’s membership of the European Union. Your 
[normal]Committee
[normal] would do well to make this point. 
